nodes.text: I've had customers in similar predicaments where they didn't want to go for the extra add-ons, but once they learned the value they could bring to their drive, they were turned around to go for it! Sounds like between swim team and your excellence in the office, some extra support on the road can be the best way to go for the gold! What do you say?
nodes.feedback: Referencing other customer experiences is a better flex to an Expressive than an Analytical.

nodes.content: You show Priscilla the details about the add-on, and she is happy to learn that it'll save her future headaches by lasting longer than other wheels. Priscilla thanks you for your patience as she drives her new SUV off the lot.

nodes.text: This add-on is specifically catered to drivers who are going long distances. From what you've shared, this may come in handy for trips to swim meets or conferences. I know you've had your eye on this vehicle for a while, and I'd hate for you to have to delay your search. If you'd like I can provide further details comparing these add-ons to the base model wheels so you can learn more of their perks and advantages. Does that sound like a good plan to you?
